	(text "IMPORTANT: For redundancy, as\nmany power sources available\nas possible are taken and used.\n\nTo monitor power usage throughout\nflight, the VBAT runs through\nthe INA226 power monitor, then\ngoes to motors WITHOUT a diode.\n(Otherwise diodes would have to\ndrop ~30A worth of 0.7V)\n\nThe ESC PWM 5V outputs also\nprovide the option of latching\nonto the +5V line with a\nsolder connection incase the\n5V regulator doesn't work.\n\nVBUS (USB) doesn't go through\nthe monitor because USB will not\nbe used during flight. So,\nit connects straight to VSYS,\nwhich is the rest of the system,\nusing a diode to stop feedback\nwhen BAT and USB are both\nconnected.\n\nIn the case of\nthe ESC 5V being\nused, the ESCs run\noff of VMOTORS\nso they would be\ncounted in the\npower measurment\nas well."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 180.848 184.912 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 0.635 0.635)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "6117d020-fe7c-436f-bfe3-3270b7fc9788")
	)
